ZH: 俗话说，吃得苦中苦，方为人上人。
EN: As the saying goes, no pain no gain.

ZH: 俗话说，有志者，事竟成。
EN: As the saying goes, where there's a will, there's a way.

ZH: 俗话说，近朱者赤，近墨者黑。
EN: As the saying goes, a man is known by the company he keeps.

ZH: 俗话说，人无远虑，必有近忧。
EN: As the saying goes, take care of the future when the present is well.

ZH: 俗话说，败者为寇，胜者为王。
EN: As the saying goes, to the victor belong the spoils.

ZH: 俗话说，谁言寸草心，报得三春晖。
EN: As the saying goes, one good turn deserves another.

ZH: 俗话说，酒香也怕巷子深。
EN: As the saying goes, even good wine can't go unappreciated if it's kept hidden.

ZH: 俗话说，知足者常乐。
EN: As the saying goes, contentment is wealth.

ZH: 俗话说，枪打出头鸟。
EN: As the saying goes, the nail that sticks out gets hammered down.

ZH: 俗话说，马到成功。
EN: As the saying goes, success comes to those who work hard.

ZH: 俗话说，饥寒交迫。
EN: As the saying goes, when it rains, it pours.

ZH: 俗话说，知己知彼，百战不殆。
EN: As the saying goes, know your enemy and know yourself, and you can fight a hundred battles without danger of defeat.

ZH: 俗话说，一分钟在人间，一年在世间。
EN: As the saying goes, a minute on the stage, a year in the audience.

ZH: 俗话说，夜深人静。
EN: As the saying goes, silence speaks louder than words.

ZH: 俗话说，金无足赤，人无完人。
EN: As the saying goes, there is no such thing as a perfect person or a perfect situation.

ZH: 俗话说，事情非独立。
EN: As the saying goes, everything is interconnected.

ZH: 俗话说，虚荣心，有骨无肉。
EN: As the saying goes, vanity is empty and fleeting.

ZH: 俗话说，甘瓜披霜。
EN: As the saying goes, enduring hardship leads to success.

ZH: 俗话说，自在心自在身。
EN: As the saying goes, a calm mind leads to a calm body.

ZH: 俗话说，以身试法。
EN: As the saying goes, to walk the talk.
